def: Of or pertaining to regeneration; tending to regenerate; as,regenerative influences. H. Bushnell. Regenerative furnace (Metal.),a furnace having a regenerator in which gas used for fuel, and airfor supporting combustion, are heated; a Siemens furnace.
Obtained from plants by distillation. [Obs.] Crabb.
The general appearance and manner of life of a living organism.
A country or region, more or less remote from the city of Rome,brought under the Roman government; a conquered country beyond thelimits of Italy. Wyclif (Acts xiii. 34). Milton.

The matins and lauds for the last three days of Holy Week,commemorating the sufferings and death of Christ, -- usually sung onthe afternoon or evening of Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday, insteadof on the following days.
Pertaining to, or connected with, the endoskeleton; as,endoskeletal muscles.
Of, pertaining to, or like, a wife or a woman. " Wifelikegovernment." Shak.
Consisting of two pyramids placed base to base; having apyramid at each of the extremities of a prism, as in quartz crystals.
A small collection of sheaves set up in the field; a shock; inEngland, twelve sheaves.
Of or pertaining to the pope; taught or ordained by the pope;hence, of or pertaining to the Roman Catholic Church; -- often usedopprobriously.-- Pop"ish*ly, adv.-- Pop"ish*ness, n.
